BT 1 0 0 1 8 225 Tm (Encapsulation) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 108.8 225 Tm (All 12 classes) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 231.2 225 Tm (Every field across every class is declared private. Access is controlled through getters and setters only. No class can directly modify another class's data.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 8 201 Tm (Inheritance) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 108.8 201 Tm (User ) Tj /F7 9 Tf 12 TL (\256) Tj /F1 9 Tf 12 TL ( Admin, Staff) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 231.2 201 Tm (Admin and Staff extend User. They inherit username, password, role, and the login method. Each adds its own specific behavior without rewriting what already exists.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 8 177 Tm (Abstraction) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 108.8 177 Tm (User.java) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 231.2 177 Tm (User is declared abstract. You cannot create a new User\(\) object directly anywhere in the code. The abstract method showCapabilities\(\) forces every subclass to define what it can do.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 8 153 Tm (Polymorphism) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 108.8 153 Tm (Menu.java \227 currentUser) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 231.2 153 Tm (currentUser is declared as type User. At runtime it holds either an Admin or Staff object. getRole\(\) and getUsername\(\) work correctly for both without Menu knowing which one it is.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 8 129 Tm (File I/O) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 108.8 129 Tm (FileManager.java) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 231.2 129 Tm (All five data files managed through one class. BufferedReader and BufferedWriter used for reading and writing. Append mode used for logs so data is never overwritten.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 8 105 Tm (Exception Handling) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 108.8 105 Tm (FileManager, Sales, Menu) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 231.2 105 Tm (Every file operation wrapped in try-catch for IOException and FileNotFoundException. Number input in Menu catches NumberFormatException and loops until valid input is entered.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 8 81 Tm (Array of Objects) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 108.8 81 Tm (Medicine.java) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 231.2 81 Tm (A fixed static array of 100 Medicine objects stores the full inventory. This directly demonstrates creating and managing a collection of user-defined class objects.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 8 57 Tm (ArrayList) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 108.8 57 Tm (Sales.java) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 231.2 57 Tm (An ArrayList of Bill objects stores the in-memory sales log. Loaded from file on construction. New bills added dynamically. Iterated for all report generation.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 8 33 Tm (Composition) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 108.8 33 Tm (Sales HAS-A Bill) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 231.2 33 Tm (Sales contains Bill objects \227 it creates them, stores them, and manages them. Menu contains instances of Sales, AlertSystem, and Medicine. This is HAS-A relationship in OOP.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 8 9 Tm (Static Members) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 108.8 9 Tm (Medicine.java) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 231.2 9 Tm (The inventory array, count, and idCounter are static. They belong to the class, not any single object. This means one shared inventory exists regardless of how many references are created.) Tj T* ET
